thread.title: Grain mostly higher, livestock lower

title: Grain mostly higher, livestock lower
text:
Sat, Sep 5, 2015, 6:31 AM AEST - Australia Markets closed Grain mostly higher, livestock lower Wheat, corn, oats higher, soybeans lower, on the CBOT; beef and pork lower on the CME. Associated Press – 1 hour 1 minute ago Recommend Print 
CHICAGO (AP) -- Grain futures were mostly higher Thursday on the Chicago Board of Trade. 
Wheat for December delivery rose 2.5 cents to $4.6775 a bushel; December corn was up 1.5 cents to 3.63 a bushel; December oats were up .50 cent to 2.2325 a bushel; while November soybeans declined 3 cents to $8.6650 a bushel. 
Beef and pork were lower on the Chicago Mercantile Exchange. October live cattle was off 1.13 cents to $1.4047 a pound; October feeder cattle lost 1.62 cents to $1.9570 a pound; while October lean hogs shed .30 cent to $.6915 a pound. @y7finance on Twitter, become a fan on Facebook Wall St. falls as US jobs data muddies Fed rate hike AFP
